.TH re 3 "stdlib 3.3" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
re \- Perl-like regular expressions for Erlang.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
This module contains regular expression matching functions for strings and binaries\&.
.LP
The \fBregular expression\fR\& syntax and semantics resemble that of Perl\&.
.LP
The matching algorithms of the library are based on the PCRE library, but not all of the PCRE library is interfaced and some parts of the library go beyond what PCRE offers\&. The sections of the PCRE documentation that are relevant to this module are included here\&.
.LP

.RS -4
.B
Note:
.RE
The Erlang literal syntax for strings uses the "\\" (backslash) character as an escape code\&. You need to escape backslashes in literal strings, both in your code and in the shell, with an extra backslash, that is, "\\\\"\&.

.SH DATA TYPES
.nf

\fBmp()\fR\& = {re_pattern, term(), term(), term(), term()}
.br
.fi
.RS
.LP
Opaque data type containing a compiled regular expression\&. \fImp()\fR\& is guaranteed to be a tuple() having the atom \fIre_pattern\fR\& as its first element, to allow for matching in guards\&. The arity of the tuple or the content of the other fields can change in future Erlang/OTP releases\&.
.RE
.nf

\fBnl_spec()\fR\& = cr | crlf | lf | anycrlf | any
.br
.fi
.nf

\fBcompile_option()\fR\& = 
.br
    unicode |
.br
    anchored |
.br
    caseless |
.br
    dollar_endonly |
.br
    dotall |
.br
    extended |
.br
    firstline |
.br
    multiline |
.br
    no_auto_capture |
.br
    dupnames |
.br
    ungreedy |
.br
    {newline, \fBnl_spec()\fR\&} |
.br
    bsr_anycrlf |
.br
    bsr_unicode |
.br
    no_start_optimize |
.br
    ucp |
.br
    never_utf
.br
.fi
